## 3. Sequence Diagrams

### 3a. Login Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Staff
    participant Browser
    participant AuthFilter
    participant LoginServlet
    participant StaffDAO
    participant DB as MySQL DB

    Staff->>Browser: Enter email & password → click Login
    Browser->>LoginServlet: POST /admin/login {username, password}
    LoginServlet->>StaffDAO: authenticate(username, password)
    StaffDAO->>DB: SELECT * FROM staff WHERE email=? AND password=?
    DB-->>StaffDAO: Staff row (or null)
    StaffDAO-->>LoginServlet: Staff object (or null)

    alt Login successful
        LoginServlet->>Browser: 200 OK + {role: "ADMIN" | "RECEPTIONIST"}
        Browser->>Browser: Redirect to admin-dashboard.html or receptionist-dashboard.html
    else Invalid credentials
        LoginServlet->>Browser: 401 "Invalid email or password"
    end

    Note over Browser,AuthFilter: On every subsequent request…
    Browser->>AuthFilter: HTTP Request to /admin/*
    AuthFilter->>AuthFilter: Check session for user attribute
    alt Session valid
        AuthFilter->>AuthFilter: Forward to servlet
    else No session
        AuthFilter->>Browser: Redirect to /login.html
    end
```

---

### 3b. Create Booking Flow (Receptionist/Admin)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Staff
    participant Browser
    participant BookingServlet
    participant BookingDAO
    participant DB as MySQL DB

    Staff->>Browser: Fill guest ID, room, dates → Submit
    Browser->>BookingServlet: POST /admin/bookings {action:"add", userId, roomId, checkIn, checkOut, totalPrice}
    BookingServlet->>BookingServlet: Build Booking object
    BookingServlet->>BookingDAO: addBooking(booking)

    BookingDAO->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
    BookingDAO->>DB: INSERT INTO bookings (user_id, room_id, check_in, check_out, total_price, status)
    DB-->>BookingDAO: rows affected

    alt Insert successful
        BookingDAO->>DB: UPDATE rooms SET status='Occupied' WHERE room_id=?
        DB-->>BookingDAO: rows affected
        BookingDAO->>DB: COMMIT
        BookingDAO-->>BookingServlet: true
        BookingServlet->>Browser: 200 OK
        Browser->>Browser: Refresh bookings table
    else Insert failed
        BookingDAO->>DB: ROLLBACK
        BookingDAO-->>BookingServlet: false
        BookingServlet->>Browser: 500 Internal Server Error
    end
```

---

### 3c. Process Payment & Checkout Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Staff
    participant Browser
    participant PaymentServlet
    participant PaymentDAO
    participant BookingDAO
    participant DB as MySQL DB

    Staff->>Browser: Select booking → Enter payment details → Submit
    Browser->>PaymentServlet: POST /admin/payments {bookingId, paymentMethod, amount, paymentStatus}
    PaymentServlet->>PaymentServlet: Build Payment object
    PaymentServlet->>PaymentDAO: addPayment(payment)

    PaymentDAO->>DB: INSERT INTO payments (booking_id, payment_method, amount, payment_status, NOW())
    DB-->>PaymentDAO: rows affected

    alt Payment inserted
        PaymentDAO->>DB: UPDATE bookings SET status='Completed' WHERE booking_id=?
        PaymentDAO->>DB: SELECT room_id FROM bookings WHERE booking_id=?
        DB-->>PaymentDAO: room_id
        PaymentDAO->>DB: UPDATE rooms SET status='Available' WHERE room_id=?
        DB-->>PaymentDAO: OK
        PaymentDAO-->>PaymentServlet: true
        PaymentServlet->>Browser: 200 {message:"Payment recorded successfully"}
    else Payment failed
        PaymentDAO-->>PaymentServlet: false
        PaymentServlet->>Browser: 500 {error:"Failed to record payment"}
    end
```

---

### 3d. Room Management Flow (Admin)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Admin
    participant Browser
    participant RoomServlet
    participant RoomDAO
    participant DB as MySQL DB

    %% Add Room
    Admin->>Browser: Fill room form → Add Room
    Browser->>RoomServlet: POST /admin/rooms {action:"add", roomNumber, type, price, status, description}
    RoomServlet->>RoomDAO: addRoom(room)
    RoomDAO->>DB: INSERT INTO rooms (...)
    DB-->>RoomDAO: success
    RoomDAO-->>RoomServlet: true
    RoomServlet->>Browser: 200 OK

    %% Delete Room (guarded)
    Admin->>Browser: Click Delete on a room
    Browser->>RoomServlet: POST /admin/rooms {action:"delete", roomId}
    RoomServlet->>RoomDAO: deleteRoom(roomId)
    RoomDAO->>DB: SELECT status FROM rooms WHERE room_id=?
    DB-->>RoomDAO: status

    alt Room is Occupied
        RoomDAO-->>RoomServlet: false (blocked)
        RoomServlet->>Browser: 400 "Cannot delete occupied room"
    else Room is Available / Maintenance
        RoomDAO->>DB: DELETE FROM rooms WHERE room_id=?
        DB-->>RoomDAO: success
        RoomDAO-->>RoomServlet: true
        RoomServlet->>Browser: 200 OK
    end
```

---

## Data Flow Summary

| Layer | Role | Key Classes |
|---|---|---|
| **View** | HTML/CSS/JS dashboards | `login.html`, `admin-dashboard.html`, `receptionist-dashboard.html` |
| **Controller** | Receives HTTP requests, routes actions | `LoginServlet`, `BookingServlet`, `RoomServlet`, `PaymentServlet`, `UserServlet`, `DashboardServlet` |
| **Filter** | Protects all `/admin/*` routes | `AuthFilter` |
| **DAO** | Executes SQL, returns model objects | `BookingDAO`, `RoomDAO`, `PaymentDAO`, `UserDAO`, `StaffDAO` |
| **Model** | Plain Java objects (POJOs) | `Booking`, `Room`, `Payment`, `User`, `Staff` |
| **Utility** | Singleton DB connection pool | `DBConnection` |
| **Database** | Persists all data | `oceanviewresortdb` (MySQL) |
